            "content": [
              {
                "type": "output_text",
                "text": "Contoso Electronics has implemented a Whistleblower Policy to ensure a safe and transparent working environment for all team members. Here's an overview of the policy:\n\n1. **Objective**: To encourage employees, contractors, and third parties to report unethical or illegal activities witnessed within the organization.\n  \n2. **Definition**: A whistleblower is anyone reporting activities that are illegal, unethical, or in violation of the company's policy.\n\n3. **Reporting Procedures**: \n   - Employees can report concerns by contacting the **Human Resources Department**.\n   - Alternatively, they can email the **Compliance Officer** at `compliance@contoso.com`.\n   - A confidential report can be made via the Compliance Hotline at **1-800-555-1212**.\n\n4. **Details to Include in the Report**: \n   - Time and date of the incident.\n   - The individuals involved.\n   - A description of what happened.\n   - Any evidence related to the incident.\n\n5. **Confidentiality and Non-Retaliation**: \n   - The identity of whistleblowers will remain confidential unless required otherwise by law.\n   - Retaliation against whistleblowers is strictly prohibited and will result in disciplinary action, including potential termination.\n\n6. **Investigation**: All reports will be promptly and thoroughly investigated.\n\nThis policy reinforces Contoso Electronics' commitment to ethical operations and the safety of its workplace.",
